title: R. Carlos Lamas CV
text:
Graduate Financial Economics Student  Minor In Data Science

LinkedIn Profile



Seeking Employment in Investment Research


Developed a strong understanding of financial economics that required analytical and quantitative skills.



Alternative Investing, Real Estate Finance, Algorithmic Trading.




2020 - 2024 BYU-I, Bachelor Degree in Financial Economics



June 2021 - August 2023 Etrade Financial  • Resolved customer problems related to stock and options trades  • Provided guidance on utilizing E*TRADE trading platforms for technical analysis, charting, and trade execution  • Facilitated account openings for clients ranging from day traders to high-net-worth individuals • Educated customers on retirement contributions, Roth conversions, and recharacterizations  • Investigated suspicious activities including money laundering, identity theft, and account takeovers • Assisted customers with bank wire processing and account transfers both internally and externally 



• Data Wrangling and Visualization: Preformed data analysis by cleaning and transforming data sets  • Problem-Solving: Developed analytic and critical thinking skills to break down complex problems  • Data Visualization: Visualization skills in R, PowerPoint, and Excel • Programming: Strong programming skills in R, python  • Certifications: Bloomberg Certification, Harvard Excel certification in Excel  • Languages: Fluent in Spanish  • Interests: Creating personal investment models, trading options, cooking, serving in the church, following sports • Work Eligibility: Eligible to work in the U.S. with no restrictions 


• Leadership: Proactively assisted ETRADE team members with client inquiries related to trading concepts, tax issues, and fraud-related questions. • License: Previously licensed with Series 7, Series 63, and SIE through ETRADE
Last updated: April 2024 –>
